    <p>OHANIAN: There's no jerks in the game. I mean, anybody's who's ever played pickup basketball knows that that's not always the case. And, you know, the friendships and the relationships that you build up over a number of years, it just feels right. It feels like part of my life, you know, so...</p>
    <p>BRESLOW: NPR economics correspondent John Ydstie, an all-state player in high school, has been part of my on-court life for a long, long time.</p>
