<h1> "Explosion In Heart Of Istanbul's Tourist Area Kills 10" </h1>
    <p>DAVID GREENE, HOST: </p>
    <p>A large explosion in a tourist district in Istanbul, Turkey has killed as many as 10 people. Turkish President Recep Tayyip Erdogan has blamed it on a suicide bomber with links to Syria. And Turkey's deputy prime minister said most of the dead were foreigners. We reached Erdal Karatas (ph). He is a waiter at Pasha Restaurant (ph). That's a restaurant just about 200 yards from the site of the blast in the old city of Istanbul. Thanks for joining us.</p>
    <p>ERDAL KARATAS: Good morning, hello.</p>
