    <p>BETTY RIGGINS: No.</p>
    <p>ELLIOTT: Blount is a field navigator with Enroll Alabama. There's this moment - she calls it the income dialogue - when she's on edge, hoping clients make at least $1,000 a month. Riggins barely hits the threshold.</p>
    <p>BLOUNT: OK, so that's putting us right there at 12675. So we don't hit the Medicaid gap.</p>
    <p>ELLIOTT: The Medicaid gap - people who make too much to qualify for Medicaid, but too little to qualify for federal subsidies under Obamacare.</p>
    <p>BLOUNT: It's nerve-wracking because it could be potentially heartbreaking. We, a lot of times, leave these appointments friends with these consumers and in tears.</p>
